      <lg xml:id="TolE045">
<l>ōreḻut torumoḻi yīreḻut torumoḻi</l>
<l>yiraṇṭiṟan ticaikkun toṭarmoḻi yuḷappaṭa</l>
<l>mūṉṟē moḻinilai tōṉṟiya neṟiyē</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>[One] way to classify occuring words is</l>
<l>[to classify them] as being words [formed by]</l>
<l>one vocalized symbol, words [formed by] two vo-</l>
<l>calized symbols, and words [formed by] the com-</l>
<l>bination of more than two [vocalized] symbols.<note
              place="foot">The rather ambiguous term <foreign xml:lang="ta">eḻuttu</foreign> means here ' vocalized [consonantal] symbol ' or ' vowel-symbol ' ; i.e., for the purposes of this <foreign
                xml:lang="ta">cūttiram, a, </foreign>or <foreign xml:lang="ta">ā, </foreign>or <foreign
                xml:lang="ta">ka, </foreign>or <foreign xml:lang="ta">kā </foreign>is one <foreign
                xml:lang="ta">eḻuttu</foreign> : instances : <foreign xml:lang="ta">ōreḻuttorumoḻi =
                ā </foreign>' cow ', <foreign xml:lang="ta">ka</foreign> ' protect ' ; <foreign
                xml:lang="ta">īreḻuttorumoḻi = ma-ṉi </foreign>' bell ' ; <foreign xml:lang="ta">toṭarmoḻi = ka-ṇa-vi-ri </foreign>' red orleander '.</note></l>
      </lg>
    </div>
